column1: #Text=—We have to report another exceedingly slow market.
#Text=Factors offer wheat at a reduction of ls. per qr., at which decline only a very limited business is transacted.
#Text=The average prices for the week ending February 23 were: — Wheat, 4i)s. per qr.; barley, 355. 6d.; oats, 225. 5d.; beans, 30s.
#Text=—The weather has been open and seasonable.
#Text=At this days market there was a fair attendance of the town and country trade; however, the business done was insignificant, and quite of a retail character.
#Text=Wheat may be quoted 2d. per 1001b. lower on the week, where sales were made.
#Text=Flour was held at late rates, but was difficult to move.
#Text=Oats and oatmeal, with a slow sale, barely maintained their value.
#Text=Barley, beans, and peas were neglected, and tho turn lower.
#Text=Indian coru was not mush inquired for
